There are multiple PHP syntax errors in [routes/web.php](file:///c:/Users/kj-acer/Desktop/23rd_Batch_CebuTra_Offline/routes/web.php) that trigger a `ParseError` and crash the application:

| Line | Current Code | Error Description | Correction |
|---|---|---|---|
| **43** | `Route::post('/events/store',{EventController::class,'store'})->name('events.store');` | Uses curly braces `{}` instead of array brackets `[]` for controller definition. | `Route::post('/events/store',[EventController::class,'store'])->name('events.store');` |
| **56** | `Route:middleware('auth')->group(function(){` | Missing double colon `::` for the static method call. | `Route::middleware('auth')->group(function(){` |
| **61** | `Route::put('/items/{item}',[ItineraryItemController::class,'update'])->name('items.update')` | Missing semicolon `;` at the end of the statement. | `Route::put('/items/{item}',[ItineraryItemController::class,'update'])->name('items.update');` |

