### B. Missing Backend Controllers & Models
Although [routes/web.php](file:///c:/Users/kj-acer/Desktop/23rd_Batch_CebuTra_Offline/routes/web.php) specifies routing rules for several controllers, the corresponding PHP files **do not exist** on disk. As soon as a request matches these routes, PHP will throw a `Class not found` exception.

*   **Missing Controllers in `app/Http/Controllers/`:**
    *   `TripController` (referenced for Home page and Search pages)
    *   `FavoriteController` (referenced for adding/removing favorites)
    *   `ProfileController` (referenced for profile updates)
    *   `EventController` (referenced for event details and listings)
    *   `EventCreateController` (referenced for multi-step event creation)
    *   `ItineraryController` (referenced for itineraries resource routing)
    *   `ItineraryItemController` (referenced for itinerary item creation/updates/deletions)
*   **Missing Models in `app/Models/`:**
    *   `Trip`, `Favorite`, `Event`, `Itinerary`, and `ItineraryItem` classes are entirely missing. The only model class present is `User.php`.

