## 4. Structural & View Inconsistencies

### A. Layout Duplication in `home.blade.php`
In [home.blade.php](file:///c:/Users/kj-acer/Desktop/23rd_Batch_CebuTra_Offline/resources/views/home.blade.php):
*   **Lines 1-23** extend the standard Laravel UI template:
    ```blade
    @extends('layouts.app')
    @section('content')
    ...
    @endsection
    ```
*   **Lines 27-138** suddenly restart with `<!DOCTYPE html>` and declare a separate, custom Tailwind CSS page design. 
*   **Impact:** This produces double HTML structures and rendering glitches. The page needs to be unified under a single layout wrapper (e.g., using `layouts/app.blade.php` or `layouts/dashboard.blade.php`).

### B. Missing Variables in Views
*   `home.blade.php` references `$upcomingTrips` (line 81) and `$upcomingTrips->count()` (line 77). 
*   If loaded via `HomeController` (which returns `view('home')` without variables), it will result in:
    `Undefined variable $upcomingTrips` errors.

